comments: The Prim.Int module is embedded in the PureScript compiler. Unlike `Prim`, it is not imported implicitly. It contains automatically solved type classes for working with type-level intural numbers.

declarations.comments: Compiler solved type class for adding type-level `Int`s.
declarations.title: Add

declarations.comments:
Compiler solved type class for comparing two type-level `Int`s.
Produces an `Ordering`.
declarations.title: Compare

declarations.comments: Compiler solved type class for multiplying type-level `Int`s.
declarations.title: Mul

declarations.comments: Compiler solved type class for converting a type-level `Int` into a type-level `String` (i.e. `Symbol`).
declarations.title: ToString

name: Prim.Int
